Is this population graph misleading?

[tikz]
\begin{tikzpicture}[scale=0.85]
\draw[->] (0,0)--(0,3.65);
\draw[->] (0,0)--(4.8,0);
\foreach \v/\p in {30/0,35/0.75,40/1.5,45/2.25} {\draw (-0.2,\p)--(0,\p); \node[left,font=\scriptsize] at (-0.2,\p) {$\v$};}
\fill[blue!25,draw=black] (0.6,0) rectangle (1.2,1.5);
\fill[blue!25,draw=black] (2.2,0) rectangle (4.0,2.1);
\node[below,font=\tiny] at (0.9,0) {Store A};
\node[below,font=\tiny] at (3.1,0) {Store B};
\node[rotate=90,font=\small] at (-1.0,1.1) {Sales};
\node[below,font=\small] at (2.00,-1.0) {Store};
\node[font=\scriptsize] at (2.3,3.35) {Monthly sales by store};
\end{tikzpicture}
[/tikz]
Store A sold $40$ and Store B sold $44$. Which pair of features makes this graph misleading?
